9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 203, L.D. 551, “An Act to Restore
10 Balanced Emergency Powers”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in §741-A in subsection 3 in the 3rd and 4th lines (page 1,
12 lines 37 and 38 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "The court shall expedite
13 consideration of a case brought pursuant to this subsection to the extent practicable."
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment amends the bill by removing the requirement that a court of this State
1188 expedite consideration of a case challenging the legality of an emergency order, including
1199 compliance with the limitations imposed on emergency orders.
